POLICE in Rivers State have declared a Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Port Harcourt branch driver, Barnabas Bonwin missing on duty. A statement Sunday by the Commissioner of Police (CP) Joseph Mukan, through the Rivers Command’s Spokesman, SP Nnamdi Omoni, noted that Bowin hails from Bodo, Gokana Local Government Area of Rivers. Mukan’s statement further held that, “The said Barnabas Bonwin, dark in complexion, about 6.2 fit tall and speaks Ogoni and English languages fluently was on official assignment with a Toyota Avensis car, Reg. No. RBC 522 TC that was recovered from a canal along the Mummy ‘B’ Road Port Harcourt while he was not found at the scene. “Any person with useful information as to his whereabouts should please contact Chris Onunkwo, Chief Security Officer, CBN Port Harcourt Branch on Phone Number 08038901920 or report to the nearest Police Station” Vanguard News Nigeria PORT HARCOURT—The display of N60 million, reportedly recovered by the Rivers State Police Command, after a bullion van conveying over N100 million went missing on Friday, left many dumbfounded. July 13, 2016 In "News" HOURS after Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, officially postponed Saturday's elections, the commission's office in Port Harcourt and that of the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN, remain cordoned by heavy joint military and police teams. February 16, 2019 In "News" PORT HARCOURT—Thirteen women allegedly selling the country’s currency were arrested by the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN, and the Rivers State Police Command in a joint sting operation in Port Harcourt, the state capital. December 14, 2017 In "Crime Alert"